    "slug": "foggy-weather",
    "description": "<p><strong>Foggy</strong> is pretty simple - a low-rolling, low-visbility wave of fog, obscuring vision as if you were inside a cloud. Notably, if you don't use normal ways to see and perceive, you might be at an advantage.</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Effects:</span></span></p><ul><li>Creatures without special forms of sight have -1 ACC on actions or attacks against creatures outside their Reach.</li><li>Electric-Type Attacks deal 30% less damage.</li><li>Bug-Type creatures possess Low Cover against Ranged attacks and have their SPD increased by 25%.</li><li>Psychic-Type creatures have their SPATK and SPDEF stats increased by 20%.</li><li>Sleight of Hand and Stealth rolls gain +1 DoS, and Navigate and Spot rolls lose -1 DoS.</li></ul>"
  },
